2 SENATE BILL 523
1 (B) ON REQUEST, AN EMPLOYEE SUBJECT TO THIS SECTION MAY BE
2 ENTITLED TO CANCER SCREENING LEAVE WITH PAY.
3 (C) AN EMPLOYEE MAY:
4 (1) USE UP TO 4 HOURS OF CANCER SCREENING LEAVE IN ANY
5 12–MONTH PERIOD FOR CANCER SCREENING; AND
6 (2) USE CANCER SCREENING LEAVE ONLY AFTER OBTAINING
7 APPROVAL FROM THE EMPLOYEE’S APPOINTING AUTHORITY.
8 (D) THE SECRETARY SHALL ADOPT REGULATIONS GOVERNING CANCER
9 SCREENING LEAVE, INCLUDING REGULATIONS THAT ESTABLISH CONDITIONS AND
10 PROCEDURES FOR REQUESTING AND APPROVING CANCER SCREENING LEAVE.
11 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
12 1, 2025.
